This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it focuses on automatically describing video content with natural language. The use of a dynamic attention mechanism and step-by-step learning also suggests that it may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of popular video datasets such as MSVD and MSR-VTT suggests that it may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
